MC_NPC_UPDATE.comment: (EntityNPC NPC) | Optional Arg: EntityType - Called after an NPC is updated.

MC_POST_UPDATE.comment: Callback has no arguments. Called after game update.

MC_POST_RENDER.comment: Callback has no arguments. Called after game render.

MC_USE_ITEM.comment: (CollectibleType ItemID, RNG RNG, EntityPlayer Player, UseFlags Flags, ActiveSlot Slot, integer CustomVarData): boolean | table, Optional Arg: CollectibleType - Called when a custom active item is used. The item RNG allows for the item's random events to be seeded. Return true to show the "use item" animation, otherwise false. If a table is returned instead of a boolean, the following fields can be set to a non-nil value for extra functionality: {Discharge: Determines whether the item should be discharged or not after being used, Remove: Determines whether the item should be removed from the player or not after being used, ShowAnim: Plays the default use animation if set to true (equivalent to simply returning true in AB+)}

MC_POST_PEFFECT_UPDATE.comment: (EntityPlayer Player), Optional Arg: PlayerType - Called for each player, each frame, after the player evaluates the effects of items that must be constantly evaluated.

MC_USE_CARD.comment: (Card CardID, EntityPlayer Player, UseFlags integer), Optional Arg: Card - Called when a custom card is used.

MC_FAMILIAR_UPDATE.comment: (EntityFamiliar Familiar), Optional Arg: FamiliarVariant - Called every frame for each custom familiar.

MC_FAMILIAR_INIT.comment: (EntityFamiliar Familiar), Optional Arg: FamiliarVariant - Called just after a custom familiar is initialized.

MC_EVALUATE_CACHE.comment: (EntityPlayer Player, CacheFlag CacheFlag), Optional Arg: CacheFlag. Called one or more times when a player's stats are re-evaluated. For example, this will fire after the player picks up a collectible item that grants stats or uses a stat pill.

MC_POST_PLAYER_INIT.comment: (EntityPlayer Player), Optional Arg: PlayerVariant - Called after the player is initialized.

MC_USE_PILL.comment: (PillEffect PillEffectID, EntityPlayer Player, UseFlags Flags), Optional Arg: PillEffect - Called when a custom pill is used.

MC_ENTITY_TAKE_DMG.comment: (Entity Entity, float Amount, integer DamageFlags, EntityRef Source, integer CountdownFrames): boolean, Optional Arg: EntityType - Called before new damage is applied. Return true or nil if the entity or player should sustain the damage, otherwise false to ignore it.

MC_POST_CURSE_EVAL.comment: (integer Curses) - Curses is a bitmask containing current curses. Called after Level applied it's curses. Return the new curse bitmask. Use Isaac.GetCurseIdByName to get a custom curse

MC_INPUT_ACTION.comment: (Entity Entity, InputHook InputHook, ButtonAction ButtonAction): boolean | float, Optional Arg: InputHook - This callback fires every time the game polls for a ButtonAction input, often several times per frame even for the same action. Since it has to do with polling, it fires regardless of whether or not the player is actually pressing any particular input. Return nil if you do not want to overwrite the input. If you do want to overwrite the input, then you have to return a boolean for the IS_ACTION_PRESSED (0) and IS_ACTION_TRIGGERED (1) input hooks, or a float between 0.0 and 1.0 for the GET_ACTION_VALUE (2) input hook.

MC_LEVEL_GENERATOR.comment: This callback doesn't work right now and will never be called by the game!

MC_POST_GAME_STARTED.comment: (boolean IsContinued) - This function gets called when you start a game. IsContinued is true when you continue a run, false when you start a new one.

MC_POST_GAME_END.comment: (boolean IsGameOver) - This function gets called when the game over screen appears, or when the an ending starts playing. IsGameOver is true when you died and got a game over, false when you won and got an ending.

MC_PRE_GAME_EXIT.comment: (boolean ShouldSave) - This function gets called when you quit a run. ShouldSave is true when the game would normally create a continuable save, false when it wouldn't. Called twice when the game plays an ending.

MC_POST_NEW_LEVEL.comment: Callback has no arguments. This triggers after transitioning a level or stage.

MC_POST_NEW_ROOM.comment: Callback has no arguments. This triggers after entering a room.

MC_GET_CARD.comment: (RNG RNG, Card CurrentCard, boolean Playing, boolean Runes, boolean OnlyRunes): Card - This is used for Card Pools. Because not all cards have the same chance to spawn, use RNG for seeded random and return your card id (if you don't want to change the current card, return CurrentCard or nil). If desired, Playing (can include playing cards), Runes (can include runes), OnlyRunes (only return runes) filter can be used to make your selection.

MC_GET_SHADER_PARAMS.comment: (string shaderName): table - Return a table containing a key -> value pair for custom shader parameters. Will skip remaining callbacks when returning a table.

MC_EXECUTE_CMD.comment: (string cmd, string params): string - Return a string separated by \n (newline) per output line.

MC_PRE_USE_ITEM.comment: (CollectibleType ItemID, RNG ItemRng, EntityPlayer Player, UseFlags Flags, ActiveSlot Slot, integer CustomVarData): boolean, Optional Arg: CollectibleType - Called before an item is used. Return true to prevent the default code of an item to be triggered. This will still discharge the item.

MC_PRE_ENTITY_SPAWN.comment: (EntityType Type, integer Variant, integer SubType, const Vector Position, const Vector Velocity, const Entity Spawner, integer Seed): table{ EntityType Type, integer Variant, integer Subtype, integer Seed }

MC_POST_FAMILIAR_RENDER.comment: (EntityFamiliar Familiar, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: FamiliarVariant.

MC_PRE_FAMILIAR_COLLISION.comment: (EntityFamiliar Familiar, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean, Optional Arg: FamiliarVariant - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_NPC_RENDER.comment: (EntityNPC NPC, Vector Offset, Optional Arg: EntityType).

MC_POST_NPC_DEATH.comment: (EntityNPC NPC), Optional Arg: EntityType - Gets called after the Death animation is played.

MC_PRE_NPC_COLLISION.comment: (EntityNPC NPC, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean, Optional Arg: EntityType - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_PLAYER_RENDER.comment: (EntityPlayer Player, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: PlayerVariant.

MC_PRE_PLAYER_COLLISION.comment: (EntityPlayer Player, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean, Optional Arg: PlayerVariant - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_PICKUP_RENDER.comment: (EntityPickup Pickup, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: PickupVariant.

MC_POST_PICKUP_SELECTION.comment: (EntityPickup Pickup, integer Variant, integer Subtype): table{integer Variant, integer SubType} - Called after a Pickup was chosen from a list of random pickups to be spawned. Return table nil to continue with default game code.

MC_PRE_PICKUP_COLLISION.comment: (EntityPickup Pickup, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_TEAR_RENDER.comment: (EntityTear Tear, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: TearVariant

MC_PRE_TEAR_COLLISION.comment: (EntityTear Tear, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_PROJECTILE_RENDER.comment: (EntityProjectile Projectile, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: ProjectileVariant

MC_PRE_PROJECTILE_COLLISION.comment: (EntityProjectile Projectile, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_LASER_RENDER.comment: (EntityLaser Laser, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: LaserVariant

MC_POST_KNIFE_RENDER.comment: (EntityKnife Knife, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: KnifeSubType

MC_PRE_KNIFE_COLLISION.comment: (EntityKnife Knife, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean, Optional Arg: KnifeSubType - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_EFFECT_RENDER.comment: (EntityEffect Effect, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: EffectVariant

MC_POST_BOMB_RENDER.comment: (EntityBomb Bomb, Vector Offset), Optional Arg: BombVariant

MC_PRE_BOMB_COLLISION.comment: (EntityBomb Bomb, Entity Collider, boolean Low): boolean, Optional Arg: BombVariant - Return true/false to ignore collision code (true to ignore collision, false to collide), or nil to continue the internal code.

MC_POST_FIRE_TEAR.comment: (EntityTear Tear) - Called when the player fires a tear.

MC_PRE_GET_COLLECTIBLE.comment: (ItemPoolType PoolType, boolean Decrease, integer Seed): CollectibleType - This callback is called when the game needs to get a new random item from an item pool.

MC_POST_GET_COLLECTIBLE.comment: (CollectibleType SelectedCollectible, integer PoolType, boolean Decrease, integer Seed): CollectibleType - This function is called right after MC_PRE_GET_COLLECTIBLE and determines the Collectible that will be spawned from the given ItemPoolType.

MC_GET_PILL_COLOR.comment: (PillColor SelectedPill, integer Seed): PillColor - This function is called when the game is spawning a pill and needs to determine its PillColor.

MC_GET_PILL_EFFECT.comment: (PillEffect SelectedPillEffect, PillColor PillColorID): PillEffect - Called every frame when the game gets the PillEffect of a pill. The effect of the pill can be chosen by returning the chosen PillEffect.

MC_GET_TRINKET.comment: (TrinketType SelectedTrinket, RNG TrinketRNG): TrinketType - Called when the TrinketType of a trinket needs to be determined.

MC_POST_ENTITY_REMOVE.comment: (Entity Entity), Optional Arg: EntityType - Called whenever an Entity gets removed by the game. This includes deaths, kills, removals and even unloading an entity on room transition or ending a run.

MC_POST_ENTITY_KILL.comment: (Entity Entity), Optional Arg: EntityType - Called right before a death animation is triggered for an Entity.

MC_PRE_NPC_UPDATE.comment: (EntityNPC NPC): boolean, Optional Arg: EntityType - Return true if the internal AI should be ignored, false or `nil`/nothing otherwise.

MC_PRE_SPAWN_CLEAN_AWARD.comment: (RNG Rng, Vector SpawnPos): boolean - Return true if the spawn routine after any room clear should be ignored, false or `nil`/nothing otherwise.

MC_PRE_ROOM_ENTITY_SPAWN.comment: (EntityType Type, integer Variant, integer SubType, integer GridIndex, integer Seed) - This is called when entering a new room, before spawning entities which are part its layout. Grid entities will also trigger this callback and their type will the same as the type used by the gridspawn command. Because of this, effects are assigned the type 999 instead of 1000 in this callback. Optional return: an array table with new values { Type, Variant, Subtype }. Returning a table will override any replacements that might naturally occur i.e. enemy variants.

MC_PRE_ENTITY_DEVOLVE.comment: (Entity Entity) - Return true if the internal devolving behavior should be ignored - When returning true, this callback is responsible for spawning the devolved entity and removing the original one.

MC_PRE_MOD_UNLOAD.comment: (table Mod) - This is called right before any mod is unloaded (when disabling a mod or reloading it using luamod), the mod's table is passed as an argument.

ENTITY_WALKINGBOIL.comment: ai for WalkingBoil, WalkingGut and WalkingSack

CACHE_PICKUP_VISION.comment: invalidates effects that predict pickup drops (i.e. Guppy's Eye)

CACHE_TWIN_SYNC.comment: special cache flag used when syncing Jacob and Esau's speed

GRIDCOLL_BULLET.comment: detect collision with solids (no pits), don't correct position

GRIDCOLL_GROUND.comment: collide with all grid entities (rocks, pits, ..), correct position

GRIDCOLL_NOPITS.comment: collide with all grid entities except pits and correct position

GRIDCOLL_PITSONLY.comment: moving inside a pit, collide with everything else, correct position

FLAG_NO_STATUS_EFFECTS.comment: Prevents status effects from applying to the entity (e.g. freeze, poison, slow, charm, confusion, fear, burn, etc.).

FLAG_APPEAR.comment: The "Appear" animation will be played after the entity is initialized.

FLAG_RENDER_FLOOR.comment: Meant for entities that have a sprite loaded that represent a floor texture. Entities with this flag will be removed after their first render. (Removing the entity is desirable because we would not want it to override other things that render to the floor, like bomb explosions.) You can use `EntityFlag.NO_REMOVE_ON_TEX_RENDER` to disable this behavior.

FLAG_NO_TARGET.comment: Will not be a target of NPCs or familiars.

FLAG_FEAR.comment: Fleeing in fear (from e.g. Mom's Pad).

FLAG_BURN.comment: Caused by Fire Mind tears. Works like poison except with a red color effect.

FLAG_RENDER_WALL.comment: Meant for entities that have a sprite loaded that represent a wall texture. Entities with this flag will be removed afte

FLAG_INTERPOLATION_UPDATE.comment: The entity is updating at 60 frames per second and this is an odd frame.

FLAG_APPLY_GRAVITY.comment: Indicates that the entity is in a side-scrolling room and is within a gravity zone.

FLAG_LASER_POP.comment: EntityTear: Pop tear fired by a laser, should decelerate very quickly for the first few frames

FLAG_ITEM_SHOULD_DUPLICATE.comment: EntityPickup: item pedestal affected by Damocles, will be duplicated at the end of the current frame

FLAG_BOSSDEATH_TRIGGERED.comment: Some bosses (Lamb/Mother) can die but they'll still appear to be active in the room (IsActiveEnemy). You can check this flag in those cases

FLAG_DONT_OVERWRITE.comment: Used in entityfactory to not remove this entity if there is no space left for new entity

FLAG_SPAWN_STICKY_SPIDERS.comment: Used by Sticky bombs to generate spiders on death

FLAG_SPAWN_BLACK_HP.comment: Used by black hp drop tear flag to drop a black hp on enemy death

FLAG_NO_FLASH_ON_DAMAGE.comment: Entity will not flash red when damaged

FLAG_NO_KNOCKBACK.comment: Bombs and farts have no knockback effects

FLAG_ADD_JAR_FLY.comment: Adds a fly to the jar when killed

FLAG_DONT_COUNT_BOSS_HP.comment: Do not count boss hp. If all boss entities have this tag, the boss hp bar is hidden

FLAG_CONTAGIOUS.comment: Used for Contagious item (if the enemy is infected)

FLAG_HIDE_HP_BAR.comment: Hides the Spider Mod hp bar of an EntityNPC

FLAG_NO_DAMAGE_BLINK.comment: Player was given a short period of invulnerability by something other than damage, don't blink

FLAG_PERSISTENT.comment: The entity will persists between rooms. (It will appear in every room, as opposed to the game remembering the specific room that it was spawned in.)

FLAG_BACKDROP_DETAIL.comment: Was spawned as a backdrop decoration, should be deleted if the current backdrop changes (due to Delirium)

FLAG_AMBUSH.comment: Enemy was spawned by some sort of ambush (Greed Mode, challenge rooms), don't collide with the player for a few frames

FLAG_GLITCH.comment: Glitched out, has different effects depending on the entity

FLAG_SPIN.comment: Used by Spin to Win, causes a familiar to rapidly spin around its owner

FLAG_NO_REWARD.comment: Doesn't spawn any kind of reward on death

FLAG_NO_QUERY.comment: Hide from query results. This can hide entities from things like `Isaac.FindByType` and the `MC_ENTITY_TAKE_DMG` callback. Entities will still be visible to `Isaac.GetRoomEntities` and `_UPDATE` callbacks.

FLAG_KNOCKED_BACK.comment: Strong knockback: Forcefy moved in a specified direction for a short duration

FLAG_APPLY_IMPACT_DAMAGE.comment: Inflicts damage upon colliding with enemies, takes damage when colliding with walls

FLAG_ICE.comment: Flagged to become frozen on death

FLAG_MAGNETIZED.comment: Magnetized: Attracts nearby enemies, projectiles and pickups

FLAG_BAITED.comment: Baited: Is targeted by nearby enemies

FLAG_BRIMSTONE_MARKED.comment: Marked by Tainted Azazel; takes extra damage from Brimstone attacks.

FLAG_FRIENDLY_BALL.comment: Used to detect enemies spawned by Friendly Ball

DAMAGE_ACID.comment: Damage comes from acid, e.g. blood acid

DAMAGE_RED_HEARTS.comment: Damage affects only red hearts if > 1 (ex: razor)

DAMAGE_COUNTDOWN.comment: Damage from unicorn horn, the nail, game kid that has cooldown

DAMAGE_CLONES.comment: Damage is done by clones when they took damage, avoid infinite loops

DAMAGE_DEVIL.comment: Damage comes from devil room deal

DAMAGE_ISSAC_HEART.comment: Indicates the damage has been redirected from Isaac's Heart familiar

DAMAGE_TNT.comment: Damage comes from a TNT barrel

DAMAGE_INVINCIBLE.comment: Damages even if invincible (currently only for player). Used on IV Bag.

DAMAGE_SPAWN_FLY.comment: Creates a fly when damage is applied

DAMAGE_CURSED_DOOR.comment: Damage comes from a cursed door

DAMAGE_TIMER.comment: Damage comes from the passage of time (used for player damage by time limited special seeds)

DAMAGE_IV_BAG.comment: Damage from using the IV Bag

DAMAGE_PITFALL.comment: Damage comes from pitfalls (such as ones spawned by Little Horn)

DAMAGE_FAKE.comment: Fake damage that should trigger player's damage effects.

DAMAGE_SPAWN_BLACK_HEART.comment: Should drop a black heart if damage is lethal

DAMAGE_CRUSH.comment: Damage comes from a strong impact, can damage Tuff Twins or The Shells' stony exteriors (like Mom's foot, shockwaves

DAMAGE_SPAWN_RED_HEART.comment: Should drop a red heart if damage is lethal

DAMAGE_SPAWN_COIN.comment: Should drop a coin if damage is lethal

DAMAGE_NO_PENALTIES.comment: Damage shouldn't apply any penalties (such as devil deal chance)

DAMAGE_SPAWN_TEMP_HEART.comment: Should drop a half red heart that quickly despawns if damage is lethal

DAMAGE_SPAWN_CARD.comment: Should drop a card if damage is lethal

DAMAGE_SPAWN_RUNE.comment: Should drop a rune if damage is lethal

SORTING_BACKGROUND.comment: Background level, behind grid entities (creep, pitfalls)

SORTING_NORMAL.comment: Uses Y position to determine Z sorting

NUM_BACKWARDS_STAGES.comment: Save stages up to Mausoleum II for the Ascent (7 stages)

STAGETYPE_GREEDMODE.comment: deprecated, Greed Mode no longer has its own stages

ROOM_SECRET_EXIT.comment: Trapdoor room to the alt path floors

ROOM_BLUE.comment: Blue Womb rooms spawned by Blue Key

STATE_MAX_COINS_OBTAINED.comment: set when reaching 99 coins, used to check for the Golden Razor achievement

STATE_SECRET_PATH.comment: set when entering a trapdoor that leads to the alternate path

TEAR_BIG_SPIRAL.comment: Ouroboros Worm, big radius oscilating tears

TEAR_BOOGER.comment: Booger tears, stick and do damage over time

TEAR_EGG.comment: Egg tears, leave creep and spawns spiders or flies

TEAR_ACID.comment: Sulfuric Acid tears, can break grid entities

TEAR_BELIAL.comment: Belial tears, piecing tears gets double damage + homing

TEAR_LASERSHOT.comment: Trisagion, generates a laser on top of the tear

TEAR_ORBIT_ADVANCED.comment: Orbiting tears with a more narrow and stable orbit (used by Saturnus and Immaculate Heart)

TEAR_ROCK.comment: Rock tears, chance to break rocks, deal extra damage to rock type enemies

TEAR_TURN_HORIZONTAL.comment: Brain Worm, tears turn and go horizontally when moving past an enemy

TEAR_BLOOD_BOMB.comment: Blood Bombs, leave blood creep on the ground

ONE_UP.comment: Works like RoomTransitionAnim.MAZE but plays the one up sound upon entering the room.

D7.comment: The same as RoomTransitionAnim.TELEPORT, but on Direction.NO_DIRECTION it'll play a fade to black, instead of a fade to white.

BOSS_FORCED.comment: No transition, goes directly to boss intro (for backwardass challenge)

FADE_MIRROR.comment: Plays the mirror exit sound and a fade to white animation. If used with Direction.NO_DIRECTION, the fade to white is shorter.

DEATH_CERTIFICATE.comment: The player lies down, then there's a fade to black and the player appears lying down again and gets up. Ignores the direction, but using Direction.NO_DIRECTION will make the fade shorter. The game is paused during the lying down and getting up animation.

LASER_SUBTYPE_LINEAR.comment: Typical laser that has a start and end point.

LASER_SUBTYPE_RING_LUDOVICO.comment: Controlled ring laser a la Tech+Ludovico, Brim+Ludovico

LASER_SUBTYPE_RING_PROJECTILE.comment: Ring laser that travels like a projectile (Technology X)

LASER_SUBTYPE_RING_FOLLOW_PARENT.comment: Ring lasers that encircle their parents (Maw of the Void)

LASER_SUBTYPE_NO_IMPACT.comment: For Technology Zero, doesn't create an impact

TAG_SYRINGE.comment: Syringes (for Little Baggy and the Spun! transformation)

TAG_MOM.comment: Mom's things (for Mom's Contact and the Yes Mother? transformation)

TAG_TECH.comment: Technology items (for the Technology Zero unlock)

TAG_BATTERY.comment: Battery items (for the Jumper Cables unlock)

TAG_QUEST.comment: Quest item (cannot be rerolled or randomly obtained)

TAG_MONSTER_MANUAL.comment: Can be spawned by Monster Manual

TAG_TEARS_UP.comment: Tears up item (for Lachryphagy unlock detection)

TAG_STARS.comment: Star themed items (for the Planetarium unlock)

TAG_NO_CANTRIP.comment: Can't be obtained in Cantripped challenge

TAG_WISP.comment: Active items that have wisps attached to them (automatically set)

TAG_UNIQUE_FAMILIAR.comment: Unique familiars that cannot be duplicated

TAG_NO_CHALLENGE.comment: Items that shouldn't be obtainable in challenges

TAG_NO_DAILY.comment: Items that shouldn't be obtainable in daily runs

TAG_LAZ_SHARED.comment: Items that should be shared between Tainted Lazarus' forms

TAG_LAZ_SHARED_GLOBAL.comment: Items that should be shared between Tainted Lazarus' forms but only through global checks (such as PlayerManager::HasCollectible)

TAG_NO_EDEN.comment: Items that can't be randomly rolled

CARDTYPE_SUIT.comment: Standard playing cards (twos, aces and Joker, does not include Suicide King, Rules Card or Queen of Hearts)

CARDTYPE_SPECIAL.comment: Special cards (anything that doesn't fall in the above categories excludes non-cards such as Dice Shard, see below)

CARDTYPE_SPECIAL_OBJECT.comment: Special pocket items that do not qualify as "cards"

RENDER_NORMAL.comment: Rendering room entities normally (in a dry room)

RENDER_WATER_ABOVE.comment: Rendering room entities above the water in a flooded room

RENDER_WATER_REFRACT.comment: Rendering room entities below the water in a flooded room. Unused

RENDER_WATER_REFLECT.comment: Rendering the reflection of room entities in a flooded room
